<DocsLayout
  title="Contributing | better-worktree"
  description="How to build better-worktree from source and contribute changes."
  pageTitle="Contributing"
>
  <p class="muted">
    Use this guide if you want to build the tool locally, run verification, or open a pull
    request.
  </p>

  <h2>Local development setup</h2>
  <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/your-org/better-worktree.git
cd better-worktree
bun install</code></pre>

  <h2>Run the apps</h2>
  <pre><code>bun run start      # CLI + TUI
bun run docs:dev   # Docs site</code></pre>

  <h2>Required verification</h2>
  <pre><code>bun test
bunx tsc --noEmit</code></pre>

  <h2>Before opening a PR</h2>
  <ul class="muted">
    <li>Add or update tests for behavior changes.</li>
    <li>Keep changes focused and include a clear description of intent.</li>
    <li>Update docs when command behavior or workflows change.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Detailed guide</h2>
  <p class="muted">
    For repository-level contribution policies, see <code>CONTRIBUTING.md</code> in the project
    root.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
